 String.prototype.replaceAll()

 replaceAll in JavaScript is a function that replaces all occurrences of a specified value with another value in a given string.

 Replacing all occurrences of a word:
 const originalString = "Hello, world! Hello again.";

 Replacing multiple spaces with a single space:
 const text = "This   has   extra       spaces.";


  Logical Assignment Operators (||=, &&=, ??=)


 Logical OR-Assignment (||=): This operator assigns the value of its right-hand operand to its left-hand operand if the left-hand operand
 evaluates to a falsy value (false, null, undefined, 0, '', NaN). Otherwise, it leaves the left-hand operand unchanged.

 Logical AND-Assignment (&&=): This operator assigns the value of its right-hand operand to its left-hand operand if the left-hand operand
 evaluates to a truthy value. Otherwise, it leaves the left-hand operand unchanged.


  Numeric Separators

  This feature allows underscores (_) to be used as separators within numeric literals to improve readability.

  code:------------------
  // 2021
// replaceAll()
const originalString = "Hello, world! hello again.";
const newString = originalString.replaceAll("hello","hi");
console.log(newString); // Hello, world! hi again.

// Replacing multiple spaces with a single space:
// between letter space is there so we can remove by this..

const text = " This    has   extra       spaces";
const normalizedText = text.replaceAll(/\s+/g," ") //  '\s' is space
console.log(normalizedText); // This has extra spaces


